title: Fishhook, "Fish hooks, Solomon Islands", Before 1917
medium: Carved turtle shell, mother-of-pearl, glass beads, fiber cord
dimensions: H x W x D: 2.5 x 1.4 x 8.3 cm (1 in. x 9/16 in. x 3 1/4 in.)
creditline: Department of Anthropology, National Museum of Natural History, Smithsonian Institution, E399972
description: Fish hook made in two parts, a hook of turtle shell and a shank lure of mother-of-pearl made to look vaguely insect-like with short antennae of strings of blue beads ending in tufts of red thread. Collector indicated that this fish hook came from one of four islands, San Christoval, New Georgia, Santa Anna, or Anki-Malaita.
